<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - CHECKING THE FLYWHEEL HOUSING - CHECKING CRANKSHAFT PILOT CONCENTRICITY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="3">
        <title>CHECKING CRANKSHAFT PILOT CONCENTRICITY</title>
        <para>Check flywheel crankshaft flywheel pilot concentricity as follows. Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600729">7.29</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            :
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator to flywheel housing and place tip up against flywheel pilot.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft slowly and record the total indicator variation. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>
                for concentricity tolerance.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600727" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5055" filename="../figeg5/EG5055.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.27 Checking Flywheel Bore Concentricity</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600728" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5054" filename="../figeg5/EG5054.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.28 Checking Flywheel Housing Face Runout</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600729" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5056" filename="../figeg5/EG5056.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.29 Checking Flywheel Housing Pilot Concentricity</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
